The paper discusses a data structure (pairing heaps) and its performance analysis, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and algorithm analysis (cs.AL). The use of a new potential function may also relate to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the analysis of the amortized costs involves mathematical techniques such as logarithms and exponentials, which may also fall under numerical analysis (cs.NA).
